Yet when Williams went to Uganda last summer, the only scholar from Aspen to work abroad as part of a Global Pathfinder fellowship, she found familiarity and support.

"People who have never left their country aren't judgmental at all," she said. "They focus more on building a relationship."

A fair spread: Over 2,000 attend?

Barring rain or mold, it seems the International Education Department felt safe enough to announce a pre-event prediction of 2,000. MCPS spokesman Derek Turner couldn't have been happier with that estimate.

"It was phenomenal," said Turner. "Even the governor stopped by."
